article.headline: Chattanooga 62, Samford 59
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Gee McGhee had a team-high 14 points as Chattanooga beat Samford 62-59 in overtime Monday night. Lance Stokes and Drazen Zlovaric each scored 13 for Chattanooga (10-15, 5-7 Southern Conference). After Lance Stokes' layup with 53 seconds left put the Mocs ahead 55-53, Tim Williams converted two free throws with 42 seconds left to tie the game at 55. Raijon Kelly missed a 3-pointer for Samford sending the game into overtime. Zlovaric opened overtime with a jumper and Stokes added a free throw to put the Mocs on top 58-55 with 3:22 left. Though Kelly scored on two different occasions inside a minute to bring the Bulldogs within one, McGhee and Ronrico White each converted a pair of free throws to hold off Samford (8-17, 6-6). Down three, 62-59, with 4 second remaining, Kelly missed a potential game-tying 3-pointer. Kelly led the Bulldogs with 19 points.
